Thanks, I'll leave it for you to edit for now.  You probably want to
add the relevant color presets to the interface (5400k isn't there).
The summary good news is that ddccontrol works great with my radeon
9800 and VP930b with both i2c /dev using the radeonfb driver and PCI
using the fglrx driver...just needs someone to take the time to test
more controls for the XML file.  I did occassionally have ddccontrol
throw some weird errors about corrupted data like the one in my
original message, but when I'd run it again it would work.  

You know what would be great is if this was integrated into a
calibration program like monica
(http://www.pcbypaul.com/software/monica.html) and given a
step-by-step wizard like most tools of that sort have.

